the common council voted on february one seven to place the referendum on the ballot allowing only seven weeks of campaigning to reverse public opinion on the controversial issue an october one nine nine two poll conducted by the wisconsin state journal found five seven in support and three eight opposed with five expressing no opinion by election day of the more than five six zero zero zero voters who went to the polls five one cast ballots in opposition to the proposal while four nine voted to have the madison common council enact such a ban the campaign committee spearheaded by the wisconsin pro gun movement and nra ila relied on neighborhood canvassing direct mail and radio tv advertising to educate voters on the civil liberties implications raised by enforcement of the ban if the referendum was approved despite the surprising defeat it is expected that the madison initiative s chief proponent mayor paul soglin will attempt to have the common council enact an ordinance banning handguns downloaded from gun talk seven zero three seven one nine six four zero six a service of the national rifle association institute for legislative action washington dc two zero zero three six larry cipriani l v cipriani att com